span.p:
Package Creation
What happens here:
- Creates a container with the latest code
- Adds a unique label (commit hash) to identify this version
Technical Details:
- Creates two packages:
• timenet-dev-[commit-hash]
• timenetweb
Environment: Development
Runner: tndev
Branches: stage & master

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Automated Testing
What happens here:
- Runs automatic checks on the code
- Makes sure everything works correctly
Technical Details:
- Runs PHPUnit Tests
- Uses the version-specific package
Environment: Testing
Runner: tndev
Branch: stage only

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Deploy to Test Environment
What happens here:
- Sets up a test website
- Uses a temporary web address
Technical Details:
- Environment: staging-[commit-hash]
- Uses staging configuration file
- URL: http://[commit-hash].staging.timenetweb.tu-ilmenau.de
Environment: Staging
Runner: tndev
Branch: stage only

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Remove Test Environment
What happens here:
- Cleans up the test website
- Removes temporary setup
Note: Requires manual approval
Technical Details:
- Removes staging environment
- Cleans up Docker containers
Environment: Staging
Runner: tndev

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Launch to Live Website
What happens here:
- Updates the real website
- Goes live for all students
Technical Details:
- Environment: production
- Uses production configuration file
- URL: https://[timenet.tu-ilmenau.de]/
Environment: Production
Runner: tnweb
Branch: master only

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Remove from Live Website
Emergency Stop Button
Purpose:
Quick way to take down the website
if problems occur
Technical Details:
- Removes production deployment
- Manual trigger required
Environment: Production
Runner: tnweb

div.style: display: table; white-space: break-spaces; line-height: 1.5; max-width: 200px; text-align: center; width: 200px;

span.p:
Environments Explained:
- Development: Where code is packaged
- Staging: Safe testing environment
- Production: Live website for students

span.p:
Safety Features:
1. Multiple testing steps
2. Manual approvals needed
3. Emergency stop available
4. Separate test and live systems
